<oXygen:ReusableComponent id="ReusableComponent_w4r_j2c_3t">
    <oXygen:ComponentDescription></oXygen:ComponentDescription>
    <oXygen:ComponentDefinition><steps id="steps_apr_j2c_3t"><step><cmd>Navigate to the <b>Items</b> tab in the <b>eStore</b> app and click <b>New</b>.</cmd></step><step><cmd>Enter <b>Name</b> for the Shipping Rate.</cmd></step><step><cmd>Enter a <b>Display Name</b>. </cmd><info>The <b>Display Name</b> appears on the <b>eStore</b> checkout screen and on the customer's receipt. </info></step><step><cmd>Identify the <b>Shipping Carrier</b> using the <b>Item Class</b> lookup.</cmd></step><step><cmd>Enter the cost of shipping applied to the item in the <b>Item Price</b> field.</cmd></step><step><cmd>Select the <b>Business Group</b> and check the <b>Is Active</b> and <b>Is Shipping Rate</b> checkboxes.</cmd></step><step><cmd>Select the <b>Delivery Method</b> associated with the new Shipping Rate using the lookup.</cmd></step><step><cmd>Select the <b>Shipping Region</b>.</cmd></step><step><cmd>Enter the shipping item's <b>Minimum Weight</b> and <b>Maximum Weight</b>.</cmd></step><step><cmd>Select the <b>Item Weight UOM</b> (Unit of Measurement) using the picklist.</cmd><info>The <b>Item Weight UOM</b> value is used when creating an eStore item that requires shipping and when creating a Shipping Rate item. Admins do not have to use the same units for items and Shipping Rates. For example, the Shipping Rate might be defined in pounds and the <b>Item Weight</b> in ounces. The system performs the conversion on the backend and will apply the correct rate in the <b>eStore</b> checkout, regardless of the unit. </info></step><step><cmd>The new Shipping Rate inherits the GL Accounts of the associated Shipping Carrier. To override and link to an alternative account, select the GL account using the <b>Income Account</b> and <b>Refund/Credit Account</b> lookups.  Click <b>Save</b>.</cmd><info><image href="../../assets/screenshots/estore/shipping_rate_win16.png" width="600" id="image_a4v_r1c_3t"/></info></step></steps></oXygen:ComponentDefinition>
</oXygen:ReusableComponent>